Package: psplinePsd
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian P-splines for spectral density estimation
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Patricio Maturana Russel [aut, cre],
        Renate Meyer [aut]
Maintainer: Patricio Maturana Russel <p.russel@auckland.ac.nz>
Description: Implementation of a Metropolis-within-Gibbs MCMC algorithm to estimate the spectral density of a stationary time series via P-splines.  The algorithm updates a nonparametric B-spline prior using the Whittle likelihood to produce pseudo-posterior samples and is based on the work presented in Maturana Russel, P. and Meyer, R. ArXiv.  This package follows bsplinePsd package structure.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Imports: Rcpp, expm, fields
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
NeedsCompilation: yes
